Chinese President Leaves for Visit to Russia , Japan
BEIJING , November 22 ( Xinhua ) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin left here this afternoon by a special flight for Moscow for a Sino-Russian informal summit , at the invitation of Russian President Boris Yeltsin .
After his visit to Russia , President Jiang will pay a state visit to Japan at the invitation of the Japanese government .
Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and Vice-President Hu Jintao were among those seeing President Jiang off at the Great Hall of the People .
President Jiang 's entourage includes his wife Wang Yeping and Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen .
During President Jiang 's visit to Japan , he is expected to meet with Emperor Akihito and confer with Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi and other Japanese leaders .
